gomodel:SYNGO_335  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: A fusion construct of the beta4 subunit with GFP at its N terminus was overexpressed in low density hippocampal cultures (viral infection). This displayed a punctate pattern in axons and showed partial colocalization with the synaptic vesicle marker synaptobrevin II (antibody staining).\n\n30/6/2017 Pim\n- In these experiments only the presynaptic neuron is labeled (low density cultures, not all cells infected with the virus). This way co-localization observed with this \"sub-resolution\" technique can be explained as \"presynaptic\" localization.. Experimental description: Continental hippocampal cultures were prepared from rat brains. After 9-14 days in culture cells were infected with activated Semliki Forest virus containing the appropriate cDNAs.\n\n30/6/2017 Pim\nOver-expressed protein is of rat species: \"The rat β4 cDNA (13) was amplified with the following primer pairs, ....\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_335" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

